HEADWORD: Hyperbolically
<hw>Hy`per*bol"ic*al*ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Math.)</fld> <def>In the form of an hyperbola.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Rhet.)</fld> <def>With exaggeration; in a manner to
